body.name: Moons Duets Tampon Plus Liner System | Compact Tampons with Slim Liners in Soft Pouch Combo | No Toxins, Bleaches or Perfumes | Ultimate Leak Protection (32 Count | 16 tampons, 16 Liners)
features: MEET DUETS, BETTER PERIOD CARE: A tampon + liner Tandem Protection System designed by women; duets promises ultimate coverage, convenience, and confidence
NO ICKY STUFF: Designed by women, OBGYN recommended; we only make products we use ourselves, so no toxins, no elemental chlorine bleaching or perfumes, and water based inks only

A SUPERIOR TAMPON: Easy to insert and comfortable to wear for up to 8 hours, our non toxic capsule tampon has a sleek compact applicator and side to side expanding comfort core that adapts to properly fit your body
PLUS A HIGH PERFORMING LINER: Our thin liners catch leaks and keep you protected with a super absorbent core and flexible exterior layer; they stay securely in place with any style of undies

2 IN 1 DUETS POUCH: Uniquely built to beautifully and discretely hold our individually wrapped tampon and liner, the duetsTM pouch is made with a quiet touch material that can be reused for easy disposal

manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: Convenient & Innovative duets is a two-product system designed by women who were tired of leaks. Each duets pouch holds a compact tampon AND a slim liner, so you always have the backup you need. Easy & Discrete Made from soft touch wrappers that tear open easily and quietly, duets pouches are also in a minimalist white, so no more hiding products up your sleeve on the way to the bathroom. No shame here! Safe & Effective Each of our products meets the highest federal safety standards. This includes individually wrapping each liner and tampon within the duets pouches and packing a helpful user guide in each box. Twice the Protection (& Confidence) No more rushing to the bathroom the second you fear a leak—using the slim liner in each duets pouch as well as the tampon gives you the backup you need, saving your time and your undies.

Designed by Women We are proud to be a female owned and operated company, and work hard to ensure that our products are designed by the folks that will actually use them! Loved by OBGYNs We’re lucky to work with some incredible, board-certified OBGYNs who make sure everything we do is medically correct and supportive of equitable health practices. On A Mission With innovative menstrual products and thoughtful info, we believe we can all better support and understand our own (and others’!) bodies and experiences. Made with Body- Friendly Materials No ickies! We only make products we ourselves use, so our tampons and liners are always free of any elemental chlorine, bleaching, toxins or perfumes.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 6, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars MOONS Duets is a must have!
reviews.reviewText: For all people who get their period- this product is a must have. MOONS Duets is such a brilliant product. Because the tampon and liner are conveniently packaged together, you'll never leave home without an emergency backup again. I haven't ruined a pair of underwear since I started using Duets.The packaging is absolutely beautiful- I keep the box on display in my bathroom. I love that this company is entirely run by women who are working towards ending the stigma around periods, while promoting education of women's bodies, cycles, and all things menstruation. I simply cannot say enough good things about this product and company. Make the switch to MOONS Duets, and you'll never use another period product again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 7, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great to have 2 in 1
reviews.reviewText: It's convenient to have 2 in 1 protection that come in a package

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2021
reviews.reviewText: Moons Duets Tampon Plus Liner System is a great idea: the tampon an liner are packed in a small package that fits in your pocket or purse easily and contains everything you need when you need it.The tampons have a plastic applicator that's easy to use, and the liners remind me of Kotex - they are barely there, but are great for peace of mind and backup protection.Moons tampons themselves are not my favorite, but they are convenient for sure.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for work!
reviews.reviewText: This is a GREAT set to keep at my work desk. For the price, I wouldn't recommend as your at home tampons. You're much better off buying tampons and a pack of liners separately for a better price, for home.For work, though (or traveling), this set is perfection. So easy to just grab one item to shove in my pocket during that week, than to grab multiple things.Liner isn't super absorbent, but perfect for catching a small leak until you change again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 25, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Nothing there to justify the cost
reviews.reviewText: Too much money for too little coverage. Solid idea, poor implementation. The liner is small and thin. The tampon is like any other cheap style. There's nothing to justify the cost, especially as other all-cotton options cost significantly less.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for travel/work
reviews.reviewText: This "system" is simple in its idea - a tampon + a liner in one pack. This is small, discreet, and easy to carry. Perfect for travel, work, the gym, festivals, and more. I like the convenience of being able to toss this in a bag and go. I don't have to hunt down multiple products to stock my bag.Absorbency is good - no leaks with the tampon. The liner is thin, but it protects underwear from stains.Overall these work well and are nontoxic. Great product!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars nice combo set!
reviews.reviewText: I love that this set has both a pad and a tampon in each packet! Both the tampon and pad are individually wrapped so, that can be used at separate times if needed. The tampon is easy to insert and comfortable once in place. The tampon is absorbent enough to last about 6 hours on my heaviest flow days. The pad is very thin but it adheres well to my underwear and protects them from spotting.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars good but not that special
reviews.reviewText: I used this thinking what makes this different/cool / revolutionary and worthy of the "moon" marketing. These are good tampons but nothing really special, in my opinion. they are a mix of polyester and cotton so not special in that regards, they are mostly synthetic. THe applicator is a lot of plastic, I mostly prefer low waste period products, they could really work on that. THat being said, the applicator does work very well. It is convenient having the thing liner and the tampon together, especially for travel. This is a good set but doesn't fo above and beyond the moon.
